      "id": "news-1",
      "title": "Kevin Garnett Wins 2003-04 NBA MVP in Unanimous Fashion!",
      "content": "Minnesota Timberwolves superstar forward Kevin Garnett has officially been named the NBA Most Valuable Player for the 2003-2004 season. Garnett put on a historic individual campaign, carrying the Timberwolves to the top seed in the deep Western Conference. Garnett led the league in double-doubles, displaying exceptional versatility, defensive dominance, and emotional leadership. Head coach Flip Saunders highly commended Garnett, calling him 'the ultimate franchise teammates of this generation.'",
      "date": "2004-05-03",
      "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1546519638-68e109498ffc?w=1000&auto=format&fit=crop&q=80",
      "category": "League MVP",
      "teamId": "minnesota-timberwolves"
    },
    {
      "id": "news-2",
      "title": "Detroit Pistons Swap Roster Assets to Landing Rasheed Wallace",
      "content": "In a frantic deadline transaction that shocked the Eastern Conference, Detroit Pistons GM Joe Dumars acquired former All-Star forward Rasheed Wallace. Wallace, who played briefly for Atlanta, completes a Detroit front-court pairing with Defensive Player of the Year contender Ben Wallace. Analysts believe this unique arrangement elevates Detroit to immediate title favorite status alongside the mighty Indiana Pacers.",
      "date": "2004-02-19",
      "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1505666287802-931dc83948e9?w=1000&auto=format&fit=crop&q=80",
      "category": "Trade Alert",
      "teamId": "detroit-pistons"
    },
    {
      "id": "news-3",
      "title": "LeBron James Makes Splash in Sensational Rookie Debut",
      "content": "The highly anticipated high-school phenom LeBron James delivered on all promises, dropping 25 points, dishing 9 assists, and grabbing 6 rebounds in his official debut for the Cleveland Cavaliers against Sacramento. Despite a narrow loss, Sacramento's head coach Rick Adelman remarked: 'He's the real deal. His passing and visual awareness are well beyond his real age.' The Rookie of the Year race with Carmelo Anthony is officially underway.",
      "date": "2003-10-30",
      "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1519766304817-4f37bda74a27?w=1000&auto=format&fit=crop&q=80",
      "category": "Rookie Debut",
      "teamId": "cleveland-cavaliers"
    }
  ],
